# PHP Social Messenger - Improved Architecture Implementation

## Problem Description

Recreate the [php-social-messenger](https://github.com/Iqbolshoh/php-social-messenger) chat application with improved architecture, security, and code quality while preserving all original functionality.

### Original Features to Preserve
- ✅ Real-time messaging (AJAX polling)
- ✅ User registration and login
- ✅ Profile management (edit name, password, picture)
- ✅ Contact search and management
- ✅ Message operations (send, edit, delete, copy, clear)
- ✅ Block/unblock users
- ✅ Unread message counts
- ✅ View user profiles

---

## Original Architecture Analysis

### Current Structure (Issues Identified)

| Issue | Description | Severity |
|-------|-------------|----------|
| **Weak Password Hashing** | Uses HMAC-SHA256 with hardcoded key "iqbolshoh" | 🔴 Critical |
| **SQL Injection Vectors** | Table/column names passed directly in queries | 🔴 High |
| **XSS Vulnerabilities** | Message content not sanitized on output | 🔴 High |
| **No CSRF Protection** | Forms lack CSRF tokens | 🟡 Medium |
| **Monolithic Structure** | PHP + HTML + JS mixed in single files | 🟡 Medium |
| **No Input Validation** | Server-side validation incomplete | 🟡 Medium |

### How Real-Time Chat Works (Original)
```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant Browser
    participant Server
    participant Database
    
    loop Every 1 second
        Browser->>Server: AJAX fetch_messages.php
        Server->>Database: SELECT messages
        Database-->>Server: Messages data
        Server-->>Browser: JSON response
        Browser->>Browser: Update DOM
    end
```

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Real-Time Technology Choice**: The original uses AJAX polling (1-second intervals). I'll preserve this for simplicity and PHP compatibility. WebSockets would require additional server setup (Node.js/Ratchet).

> [!WARNING]
> **Database Migration**: The improved version uses bcrypt for passwords. Existing demo users will have new passwords set. Default password: `Password123!`

