### Core Components

#### [NEW] [Database.php](file:///media/swastik/focus/chat%20app/php-social-messenger/src/Core/Database.php)
- PDO-based database connection with prepared statements
- Proper error handling with exceptions
- Singleton pattern for connection reuse

#### [NEW] [Session.php](file:///media/swastik/focus/chat%20app/php-social-messenger/src/Core/Session.php)
- Secure session management
- CSRF token generation and validation
- Session regeneration on login

#### [NEW] [Validator.php](file:///media/swastik/focus/chat%20app/php-social-messenger/src/Core/Validator.php)
- Input sanitization and validation
- XSS prevention with proper escaping
- Email, username, password validation rules

---

### Models

#### [NEW] [User.php](file:///media/swastik/focus/chat%20app/php-social-messenger/src/Models/User.php)
- `register($fullName, $email, $username, $password)` - bcrypt hashing
- `login($username, $password)` - Timing-safe verification
- `updateProfile($userId, $data)` - Profile updates
- `findByUsername($username)` / `findById($id)`

#### [NEW] [Message.php](file:///media/swastik/focus/chat%20app/php-social-messenger/src/Models/Message.php)
- `send($senderId, $receiverId, $content)` - XSS-safe content storage
- `getConversation($userId1, $userId2)` - Fetch messages
- `edit($messageId, $userId, $newContent)` - Owner-only edit
- [delete($messageId, $userId)](file:///media/swastik/focus/chat%20app/original-repo/config.php#94-105) - Soft/hard delete
- `markAsRead($senderId, $receiverId)`
- `clearConversation($userId1, $userId2)`

#### [NEW] [BlockedUser.php](file:///media/swastik/focus/chat%20app/php-social-messenger/src/Models/BlockedUser.php)
- `block($blockerId, $blockedId)`
- `unblock($blockerId, $blockedId)`
- `isBlocked($userId1, $userId2)`

---

### Controllers

#### [NEW] [AuthController.php](file:///media/swastik/focus/chat%20app/php-social-messenger/src/Controllers/AuthController.php)
- Login with rate limiting
- Registration with email/username uniqueness
- Logout with session destruction
- CSRF token validation on all POST requests

#### [NEW] [ChatController.php](file:///media/swastik/focus/chat%20app/php-social-messenger/src/Controllers/ChatController.php)
- RESTful API endpoints for messages
- Authorization checks (own messages only)
- Block status verification before sending

---

### Security Improvements

| Feature | Original | Improved |
|---------|----------|----------|
| Password Hashing | HMAC-SHA256 (static key) | bcrypt with cost 12 |
| SQL Queries | String concatenation | PDO prepared statements |
| XSS Prevention | Partial htmlspecialchars | Full output escaping |
| CSRF Protection | None | Token-based validation |
| Session Security | Basic | Regeneration + httpOnly cookies |
| Input Validation | Client-side only | Server-side + client-side |

---

### Database Schema (Improved)

```sql
-- Users table with improved security
CREATE TABLE users (
    id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
    full_name VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL UNIQUE,
    username VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL UNIQUE,
    password VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,  -- bcrypt hash
    profile_picture VARCHAR(255) DEFAULT 'default.png',
    is_active BOOLEAN DEFAULT TRUE,
    last_seen TIMESTAMP NULL,
    created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
    updated_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP ON UPDATE CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
    INDEX idx_username (username),
    INDEX idx_email (email)
);

-- Messages with improved indexing
CREATE TABLE messages (
    id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
    sender_id INT NOT NULL,
    receiver_id INT NOT NULL,
    content TEXT NOT NULL,
    status ENUM('unread', 'read', 'deleted') DEFAULT 'unread',
    created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
    updated_at TIMESTAMP NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (sender_id) REFERENCES users(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    FOREIGN KEY (receiver_id) REFERENCES users(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    INDEX idx_conversation (sender_id, receiver_id),
    INDEX idx_unread (receiver_id, status)
);

-- Block users with unique constraint
CREATE TABLE blocked_users (
    id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
    blocker_id INT NOT NULL,
    blocked_id INT NOT NULL,
    created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
    FOREIGN KEY (blocker_id) REFERENCES users(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    FOREIGN KEY (blocked_id) REFERENCES users(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    UNIQUE KEY unique_block (blocker_id, blocked_id)
);
```

